Creating the Laravel manifest now, then I’ll sanity-check the JSON so it’s ready to use.

The direct patch write was blocked by filesystem permissions, so I’m checking ownership and access before retrying the file creation.

I found the repo is writable, so I’m falling back to a shell write and immediate JSON validation to get the manifest in place cleanly.

The workspace is refusing direct writes, so I’m retrying with the patch tool using a repo-relative path in case the restriction is path-specific.

